nuke:
{{doc-special|Nuke}}
The Nuke extension allows for sysops to delete a large number of pages ("Mass delete").
For more information, see https://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:Nuke
{{Identical|Mass delete}}

nuke-tools-prompt-restricted:
Instructions to show to the user in the 'prompt/list' part of Special:Nuke when the user does not have the necessary permissions to delete pages, or an active block effects their ability to do this. They can only use the tool to list pages. 

See also:
* {{msg-mw|nuke-tools-confirm}}

nuke-nolist:
Used if the user clicked on 'Continue' without first listing pages.

Refers to {{msg-mw|Nuke-submit-list}}.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nopages-global}}
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-noselected}}

nuke-nopages-global:
Used if there are no pages to delete and the username is empty.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nolist}}
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-noselected}}

nuke-noselected:
Used if the user clicked on 'Continue' without selecting pages to delete.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nolist}}
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nopages-global}}

nuke-associated-limited:
Used if the user selected talk pages or redirects to be included in deletion, but some pages could not be shown because including them would go over the limit.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nolist}}
* {{msg-mw|Nuke-nopages-global}}

nuke-viewchanges:
Used as link text.

The link points to History page of the page.

This message follows:
* {{msg-mw|nuke-editby}} and {{msg-mw|comma-separator}}
* or empty string (if username is empty).
{{Identical|View changes}}
